channel.title: Wtf, it's somehow offline
channel.description:
K my server was working all nicey-nicey. Then I restart the computer because I didn't want to be in safe mode anymore. So I turn on my server. 5 minutes passes by with 0 online, so I checked canyouseeme.org and it said it couldn't see me, wtf did I do wrong? My IPv4 address didn't change, it's still 192.168.2.103, I checked my firewall and it allows port 5555... Am I getting ddosed? My server upstairs works completely fine... :S
Any help is appreciated..

item.title: Wtf, it's somehow offline
item.dc:creator: @Fridder Fridder
item.description:
@Fridder wrote:

[quote=“Davidi2, post:5, topic:400500”]I’d check and double check your internal IP address (your 192 address) to make sure it still matches your port forwarding. I know sometimes when I restart my computer my router likes to play tricks on me…

If it did change, you can follow my How to Give Yourself a Static IP Adress tutorial.

If not, again check your portfowarding and make sure it matches your server port (its usually 43594, not 5555, but you may have changed that?)[/quote]

Thanks man I’ll check this out tomorrow.
